In response to the coronavirus (COVID-19) crisis, passengers (except Turkish nationals or residents of Turkey) who have transited through or have been in the UK or other banned countries in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit or enter Turkey. Options for leaving Turkey are becoming increasingly limited and if you wish to leave Turkey you should make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
Repatriation flights from Istanbul and Antalya to the UK will continue until 24 March. Options for leaving Turkey are becoming increasingly limited and if you wish to leave Turkey you should make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
From 27 March, Turkish Airlines will only operate flights to five locations: Hong Kong, Moscow, Addis Ababa, New York and Washington.
You should check with your airline before travelling.
For the latest information about flight availability, please refer to the most recent social media updates from the Consul General in Istanbul.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
